<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3375] Python TJSONProtocol encodes utf8 string values in an incompatible way</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3375</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It uses &lt;b&gt;json.dump&lt;/b&gt; method with &lt;b&gt;ensure_ascii=True&lt;/b&gt; (via default arg) that escapes utf8 characters.&lt;br/&gt;
And yet, many implementations including Python does not attempt to unescape those characters so cannot talk to each other nor to itself, if the value has any utf8 character.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
